text.paragraph:
Pediatric patients may be more susceptible to systemic toxicity 
								from use of topical corticosteroids. [see Use in Specific Populations (8.4)
                           ]

Topically applied Clobetasol propionate cream, 0.05% (emollient) can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects 
						[see Warnings and Precautions (5.1)
                     ].
